{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb869b81e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1381"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1381"},"text":"§ 1381.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Statement of purpose; authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of establishing a national program to provide supplemental security income to individuals who have attained age 65 or are blind or disabled, there are authorized to be appropriated sums sufficient to carry out this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb869b81f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title XVI, § 1601, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1465"},"text":"86 Stat. 1465","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb869b820-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb869b821-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb869b822-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 1381, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531/tXVI/s1601"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531, title XVI, § 1601","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-07-25"},"text":"July 25, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/543/tI/s141/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–543, title I, § 141(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/197"},"text":"76 Stat. 197","children":[],"tail":", authorized appropriations for grants to States for aid to aged, blind, or disabled, and for medical assistance for aged, prior to the general amendment of title XVI of the Social Security Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, § 301","children":[],"tail":", but is set out as a note below in view of its continued applicability to Puerto Rico, Guam, and the Virgin Islands."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb869b823-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb869b824-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1465"},"text":"86 Stat. 1465","children":[],"tail":", provided that this section is effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb869b825-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Continuation of Federal Financial Participation in Experimental, Pilot, or Demonstration Projects Approved Before October 1973, for Period On-and-After ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", Without Denial or Reduction On Account Of Subchapter XVI Provisions; Waiver of Subchapter XVI Restrictions for Individuals; Federal Payments of Non-Federal Share as Supplementary Payments"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subchapter provisions without effect on Federal Financial Participation in Experimental, Pilot or Demonstration Projects approved before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1973","children":[],"tail":", for period on-and-after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/233/s11"},"text":"section 11 of Pub. L. 93–233","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/958"},"text":"87 Stat. 958","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1315"},"text":"section 1315 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb869b826-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Application to Northern Mariana Islands","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For applicability of this section to the Northern Mariana Islands, see section 502(a)(1) of the Covenant to Establish a Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands in Political Union with the United States of America and Proc. No. 4534, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-10-24"},"text":"Oct. 24, 1977","children":[],"tail":", 42 F.R. 6593, set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of Title 48","children":[],"tail":", Territories and Insular Possessions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb869b827-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Puerto Rico, Guam, and Virgin Islands","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Enactment of section 1601 of the Social Security Act by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1381"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1381","children":[],"tail":"), was not applicable to Puerto Rico, Guam, and the Virgin Islands. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/s303/b"},"text":"section 303(b) of Pub. L. 92–603","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s301"},"text":"section 301 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Therefore, as to Puerto Rico, Guam, and the Virgin Islands, section 1601 of the Social Security Act as it existed prior to reenactment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603","children":[],"tail":" (former "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1381"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1381","children":[],"tail":"), and as amended, continues to apply and reads as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"§ 1381. Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of enabling each State, as far as practicable under the conditions in such State, to furnish financial assistance to needy individuals who are 65 years of age or over, are blind, or are 18 years of age or over and permanently and totally disabled, there is hereby authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year a sum sufficient to carry out the purposes of this subchapter. The sums made available under this section shall be used for making payments to States which have submitted, and had approved by the Commissioner of Social Security, State plans for aid to the aged, blind, or disabled.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title XVI, § 1601, as added "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-07-25"},"text":"July 25, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/543/tI/s141/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–543, title I, § 141(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/197"},"text":"76 Stat. 197","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/88/tV/s509/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–88, title V, § 509(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/695"},"text":"93 Stat. 695","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXXI/s2184/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XXI, § 2184(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", title XXIII, § 2353(m)(1), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/817"},"text":"95 Stat. 817","children":[],"tail":", 873; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-15"},"text":"Aug. 15, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296/tI/s107/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296, title I, § 107(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1477"},"text":"108 Stat. 1477","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296/s107/a/1"},"text":"section 107(a)(1) of Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1995","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296/s110/a"},"text":"section 110(a) of Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 1994 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb869b828-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Payments Under Chapter Provisions in Effect Before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":", for: Activities Carried Out Through "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", Under State Plans Approved Under Subchapter I, X, XIV, or XVI Provisions; and for Administrative Activities After "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":", Closing Out Such Activities"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/233/s19/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–233, § 19(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/974"},"text":"87 Stat. 974","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/233/s19/b"},"text":"“Notwithstanding the provisions of section 301 of the Social Security Amendments of 1972 [enacting this subchapter], the Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare [now Health and Human Services] shall make payments to the 50 States and the District of Columbia after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", in accordance with the provisions of the Social Security Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s301"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] as in effect prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":", for (1) activities carried out through the close of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", under State plans approved under title I, X, XIV, or XVI, of such Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s301"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 301","children":[],"tail":" et seq., 1201 et seq., 1351 et seq., 1381 et seq.], and (2) administrative activities carried out after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1973","children":[],"tail":", which such Secretary determines are necessary to bring to a close activities carried out under such State plans.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
